\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\insrsid6574074 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6574074 PRIEST: }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid6574074 Blessed is our God, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6574074 READER:}{\cs27\i\f1\fs20\insrsid6574074 : }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  Amen. Glory to Thee, our God, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par O Heavenly King, Comforter, Spirit of Truth, Who art everywhere present and fillest all things, Treasury of good things and Giver of life: Come and dwell in us, and cleanse us of all impurity, and save our souls, O Good One. 
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done
, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.
\par  
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6574074 PRIEST: }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid6574074 For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory; of t
he Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6574074 READER:}{\cs27\i\f1\fs20\insrsid6574074 : }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  Amen.  Lord have mercy.}{\cs28\b\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074  (12 Times}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid13072411 
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par O come, let us worship God our King. 
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ our King and God.
\par O come, let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King and God. 
\par  
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 Psalm 50
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par Have mercy on me, O God, according to Thy g
reat mercy; and according to the multitude of Thy compassions blot out my transgression. Wash me thoroughly from mine iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin. For I know mine iniquity, and my sin is ever before me. Against Thee only have I sinned and done th
i
s evil before Thee, that Thou mightest be justified in Thy words, and prevail when Thou art judged. For behold, I was conceived in iniquities, and in sins did my mother bear me. For behold, Thou hast loved truth; the hidden and secret things of Thy wisdom
 
hast Thou made manifest unto me. Thou shalt sprinkle me with hyssop, and I shall be made clean; Thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow. Thou shalt make me to hear joy and gladness; the bones that be humbled, they shall rejoice. Turn Thy 
f
ace away from my sins, and blot out all mine iniquities. Create in me a clean heart, O God, and renew a right spirit within me. Cast me not away from Thy presence, and take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, and with Th
y
 governing Spirit establish me. I shall teach transgressors Thy ways, and the ungodly shall turn back unto Thee. Deliver me from blood-guiltiness, O God, Thou God of my salvation; my tongue shall rejoice in Thy righteousness. O Lord, Thou shalt open my li
p
s, and my mouth shall declare Thy praise. For if Thou hadst desired sacrifice, I had given it; with whole-burnt offerings Thou shalt not be pleased. A sacrifice unto God is a broken spirit; a heart that is broken and humbled God will not despise. Do good,
 O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings. Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }\pard\plain \s22\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 Psalm 69 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par O God, be attentive unto helping me; O Lord, make haste to help me. Let them be shamed and confounded that seek after my soul. 
\par 
\par Let them be turned back and brought to shame that desire evils against me. Let them be turned back straightway in shame that say unto me: Well done! Well done! 
\par 
\par Let them be glad and rejoice in Thee all that seek after Thee, O God, and let them that love Thy salvation say continually: The Lord be magnified. 
\par 
\par But as for me, I am poor and needy; O God come unto mine aid. 
\par 
\par My helper and my deliverer art Thou, O Lord; make no long tarrying.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 Psalm 142
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par O Lord, hear my prayer; give ear unto my supplication in Thy truth; hearken unto me in Thy righteousness. 
\par 
\par And enter not into judgment with Thy servant, for in Thy sight shall no man living be justified. 
\par 
\par For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath humbled my life down to the earth. 
\par 
\par He hath sat me in darkness as those that have been long dead, and my spirit within me is become despondent; within me my heart is troubled. 
\par 
\par I remembered days of old, I meditated on all Thy works, I pondered on the creations of Thy hands. 
\par 
\par I stretched forth my hands unto Thee; my soul thirsteth after Thee like a waterless land. 
\par 
\par Quickly hear me, O Lord; my spirit hath fainted away. 
\par 
\par Turn not Thy face away from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit. 
\par 
\par Cause me to hear Thy mercy in the morning; for in Thee have I put my hope. 
\par 
\par Cause me to know, O Lord, the way wherein I should walk; for unto Thee have I lifted up my soul. 
\par 
\par Rescue me from mine enemies, O Lord; unto Thee have I fled for refuge. 
\par 
\par Teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God. 
\par 
\par Thy good Spirit shall lead me in the land of uprightness; for Thy name's sake, O Lord, shalt Thou quicken me. 
\par 
\par In Thy righteousness shalt Thou bring my soul out of affliction, and in Thy mercy shalt Thou utterly destroy mine enemies. 
\par 
\par And Thou shalt cut off all them that afflict my soul, for I am Thy servant.
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411 
\par }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 The Doxology
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par Glory to God in the highest, and on earth, peace and good will among men.
\par 
\par  We praise Thee, we bless Thee, we worship Thee, we glorify Thee, we give thanks to  Thee for Thy great glory.
\par 
\par  O Lord, heavenly King, God the Father Almighty; O Lord, the only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ; and O Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par  O Lord God, Lamb of God, Son of the Father, that takest away the sin of the world; have mercy on us; Thou that takest away the sins of the world, receive our prayer; Thou that sittest at the right hand of the Father, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par  For Thou only art holy; Thou only art the Lord, O Jesus Christ, to the glory of God the Father.  Amen.
\par 
\par  Every night will I bless Thee, and I will praise Thy Name forever, yea, forever and forever.
\par 
\par  Lord, thou hast been our refuge in generation and generation.
\par 
\par  I said: O Lord, have mercy on me, heal my soul, for I have sinned against Thee.
\par 
\par  O Lord, unto Thee have I fled for refuge, teach me to do Thy will, for Thou art my God.
\par 
\par  For in Thee is the fountain of life, in Thy light shall we see light.
\par 
\par  O continue Thy mercy unto them that know Thee.
\par 
\par  Vouchsafe, O Lord, to keep us this night without sin.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Lord, the God of our Fathers, and praised and glorified is Thy name unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par  Let Thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we have hoped in Thee.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Lord, teach me Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Master, give me understanding of Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  Blessed art Thou, O Holy One, enlighten me by Thy statutes.
\par 
\par  O Lord, Thy mercy endureth forever; disdain not the works of Thy hands.
\par 
\par  To Thee is due praise, to Thee is due a song, to Thee glory is due, to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 The Symbol Of Faith
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par I believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and the earth and of all things visible and invisible. And in one Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of God, the Only-begotten, begotten of the Father before all ages; Light of Light, true God of true God
;
 begotten, not made; of one essence with the Father, by Whom all things were made; Who for us men and for our salvation  came down from the heavens, and was incarnate of the Holy Spirit and the Virgin Mary, and became man; And was crucified for us under P
o
ntius Pilate, and suffered and was buried; And arose again on the third day according to the Scriptures; And ascended into the heavens, and sitteth at the right hand of the Father; And shall come again, with glory, to judge both the living and the dead; W
h
ose kingdom shall have no end. And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord, the Giver of life; Who proceedeth from the Father; Who with the Father and the Son together is worshipped and glorified; Who spake by the prophets. In One, Holy, Catholic, and Apostolic Chur
ch. I confess one baptism for the remission of sins. I look for the resurrection of the dead, And the life of the age to come. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 At this point, a canon is read, being for the Theotokos, from the Oktoechos, or from the Menaion.
\par 
\par And after the canon, the Stichera from Vespers, or from the Praises of Matins if there be any appointed for the Saint.
\par 
\par Then: 
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par It is truly meet to bless thee, the Theotokos, ever blessed and most blameless, and Mother of our God. More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond comp
are more glorious than the Seraphim, who without corruption gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify.
\par 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\cs28\i\f1\fs20\cf6\insrsid6574074 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 (Thrice)}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day o
ur daily bread, and forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from the evil one.
\par 
\par }{\cs24\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6574074 PRIEST: }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384   }{\cs23\b\f1\fs34\insrsid6574074 For Thine is the Kingdom, and the power, and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit
, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par 
\par }{\cs27\i\f1\insrsid6574074 READER:}{\cs27\i\f1\fs20\insrsid6574074 : }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  Amen.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 \page If the temple be dedicated to the Lord or to the Theotokos:
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li720\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\faauto\ls8\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 the troparion of the temple is said first, 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}then the troparion of the day (see below),
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}then "O God of our Fathers...", etc. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 
\par If the temple be dedicated to a saint:
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li720\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx720\faauto\ls9\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 the troparion of the day is said first, 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}then the troparion of the temple, 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\cs28\f3\cf6 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}then "O God of our fathers...", etc. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 Troparion of the Day: 
\par 
\par On Sunday night: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par Supreme Commanders of the Heavenly Hosts, we unwort
hy ones implore you that by your supplications ye will encircle us with the shelter of the wings of your immaterial glory, and guard us who fall down before you and fervently cry: Deliver us from dangers since ye are the Marshals of the Hosts on high.

\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 On Monday night:
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par The memory of righteous is celebrated with hymns of praise, but the Lord's testimony is sufficient for thee, O Forerunner; for thou hast proved to be even more venerable than the prophets since thou wast granted to baptize in the running wat
ers Him Whom they proclaimed. Wherefore, having contested for the truth, thou didst rejoice to announce the good tidings even to those in Hades; that God hath appeared in the flesh, taking away the sin of the world and granting us great mercy.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par On Tuesday night: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par Save, O Lord, Thy people, and bless Thine inheritance; grant Thou unto Orthodox Christians victory over enemies; and by the power of Thy Cross do Thou preserve Thy commonwealth.\'b7
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 \page On Wednesday night:
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par O holy Apostles, intercede with the merciful God, that He grant unto our souls forgiveness of offenses.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 And to St. Nicholas, Fourth Tone:
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par The truth of things hath revealed thee to thy flock as a rule of faith, an icon of meekness and a teacher of tempera
nce; therefore thou hast achieved the heights by humility, riches by poverty. O Father and Hierarch Nicholas, intercede with Christ God that our souls be saved.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 On Thursday night: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par Save, O Lord, Thy people, and bless Thine inheritance; grant Thou unto Orthodox Christians victory over enemies; and by the power of Thy Cross do Thou preserve Thy commonwealth.
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 Then, Sunday night through Thursday night (if simple service):}{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par 
\par O God of our fathers, Who ever dealest by us according to Thy kindness, do not withdraw Thy mercy from us, but through their intercessions guide our life in peace. 
\par 
\par Adorned in the blood of Thy martyrs throughout all the world, as in purple and fine linen, Thy Church, through them, doth cry unto Thee, O Christ God: Send down Thy compassions upon Thy people; grant to Thy community, and to our souls great mercy. 
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing, but life everlasting. 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Through the intercessions, O Lord, of all the saints and the Theotokos, grant us Thy peace, and have mercy on us, as Thou alone art compassionate. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s29\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 On Friday night: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par O Apostles, Martyrs, and Prophets, Venerable and Righteous Ones; ye that have accomplished a good labor and kept the Faith, that have boldness before the Savior; O Good Ones, intercede for us, we pray, that our souls be saved.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit. 
\par 
\par With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing, but life everlasting.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par To Thee, O Lord, the Planter of creation, the world doth offer the God-bearing martyrs as the first-fruits of nature. By their intercessions preserve Thy Church, Thy commonwealth, in profound peace, through the Theotokos, O Greatly-merciful One. 
\par 
\par }{\cs28\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6574074 The troparion for a church patron saint is not said on Saturdays. 
\par 
\par On Saturday at Compline, the troparion and Kontakion of the Resurrection in the occurring tone are read.
\par }{\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 \page }{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 
Troparion of the Resurrection. First Tone.}{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 When the stone had been sealed by the
 Jews, and the soldiers where guarding Thine immaculate Body, Thou didst rise on the third day, O Savior, granting life unto the world. Wherefore, the Hosts of the Heavens cried out to Thee, O Life-giver: Glory to Thy Resurrection, O Christ. Glory to Thy 
kingdom. Glory to Thy dispensation, O only Lover of mankind.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. First Tone.}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 As God Thou didst arise from the tomb in glory, and Thou didst raise the world together with Thyself. And mortal nature praiseth Thee as God, and death
 hath vanished. And Adam danceth, O Master, and Eve, now freed from fetters, rejoiceth as she crieth out: Thou art He, O Christ, that grantest unto all resurrection.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Second Tone.}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 When Thou didst descend unto death, O Life I
mmortal, then didst Thou slay Hades with the lightning of Thy Divinity. And when Thou didst also raise the dead out of the nethermost depths, all the Hosts of Heavens cried out: O Lifegiver, Christ our God, glory be to Thee. 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection}{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411 
. Second Tone }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Thou didst arise from the tomb, O omnipotent Savior, and Hades was terrified on beholding the wonder; and the dead arose, and creation at the sight thereof rejoiceth with Thee. And Adam also is joyful, and world, O my Savior, praiseth Thee for ever.

\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Third Tone}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Let the heavens be glad; let earthly things rejoice; for the Lord hath wrought might with His arm. He hath trampled down death by death; the first-born of the dead hath He become. From the belly of Hades hath He delivered us and hath granted to the world 
great mercy.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Third Tone.}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Thou didst rise today from the tomb, O Merciful One, and didst lead us out of the gates of death. Today Adam danceth and Eve rejoiceth; and together with them both the Prophets and Patriarchs unceasingly praise the divine might of Thine authority.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Fourth Tone.}{
\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Having learned the joyful proclamation of the Resurrection from the angel, and having cast off the ancestral condemnation, the women disciples of the Lord spake
 to the apostles exultantly: Death is despoiled and Christ God is risen, granting to the world great mercy. 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Fourth Tone.}{
\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 My Savior and Redeemer hath, as God, raised up the earthborn from the grave and from their fetters, 
and He hath broken the gates of Hades, and, Master, hath risen on the third day.
\par }{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411 
\par Troparion of the Resurrection. Fifth Tone. }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid13072411\charrsid13072411 Let us, O faithful, praise and worship the Word Who is co-unorignate with the Father and the Spirit, and Who was born of the Virgi
n for our salvation; for He was pleased to ascend the Cross in the flesh and to endure death, and to raise the dead by His glorious Resurrection
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid13072411\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Fifth Tone.}{
\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411\charrsid7031384  }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid13072411\charrsid13072411 Unto Hades, O my Savior, didst Thou descend, and having broken it
s gates as One omnipotent, Thou, as Creator, didst raise up the dead together with Thyself. And Thou didst break the sting of death, and didst deliver Adam from the curse, O Lover of mankind. Wherefore, we all cry unto Thee: Save us, O Lord.}{
\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411\charrsid7031384 
\par }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411 
\par }{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Sixth Tone.}{\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Angelic Hosts were above Thy tomb, and they that guarded Thee became as dead. And Mary stood by the grave seeking Thine immaculate Body. Thou didst despoil Hades and wast not tempted by it. Thou didst meet the Virgin and di
dst grant us life. O Thou Who didst rise from the dead, O Lord, glory be to Thee.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Sixth Tone.}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Having by His life-bestowing hand raised up all the dead out of the dark abysses, Christ God, the Giver of Life, hath bestowed the Resurrection upon the fallen human race; for He is the Savior of all, the Resurrection, and the Life, and the God of all.

\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Seventh Tone.}{
\cs26\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384  }{\cs26\fs24\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Thou didst destroy death by Thy Cross, Thou didst open Paradise to the thief. Thou didst change the lamentation of the Myrrh-bearers, and Thou didst command Thine Apostles to proclaim that Thou didst arise, O Ch
rist God, and grantest to the world great mercy. 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Seventh Tone.}{
\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 No longer will the dominion of death be able to keep men captive; for Christ hath descended, demolishing and destroying the powers thereof. Hades is bound; the
 Prophets rejoice with one voice, saying: A Savior hath come for them that have faith. Come forth, ye faithful, for the Resurrection.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
\par }\pard\plain \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs32\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Troparion of the Resurrection. Eighth Tone.}{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{
\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 From on high didst Thou descend, O Compassionate One; to burial of three days hast Thou submitted that Thou mightest free us from our passions. O our Life and Resurrection, O Lord, glory be to Thee. }{
\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid13072411 
\par 
\par }\pard \s22\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13072411 {\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid6574074 Kontakion of the Resurrection. Eighth Tone.}{\cs28\i\fs24\cf6\insrsid13072411  }{\cs26\b0\fs24\insrsid6574074\charrsid13072411 
Having arisen from the tomb, Thou didst raise up the dead and didst resurrect Adam. Eve also danceth at Thy Resurrection, and the ends of the world celebrate Thine arising from the dead, O Greatly-merciful One.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs26\f1\insrsid6574074\charrsid7031384 
